latestPosts.caption:
my home designed by me 🩷

Radhika Seth (@radhikasethh) has her answer to the common dinner party question, “If you had to choose an alternate career, what would it be?” ready to go. The content creator-actor-podcaster-entrepreneur would happily add ‘interior designer’ to her ever-expanding repertoire. Yet, unlike most of us, Seth’s answer isn’t rooted in frivolous fantasies. When the situation presented itself, she rose to the occasion with great enthusiasm and designed her sprawling Mumbai apartment, just shy of 2,000 square feet, in an unfathomable time frame of two weeks. The result? A sleek, contemporary space swathed in shades of ecru, ivory, and beige, sprinkled throughout with Gen Z trimmings, that is wholly and truly an expression of Seth’s personality.
Soft curves, light woods, and a neutral colour palette:
Seth’s home embodies the quintessential definition of contemporary design-but only at its base. It is layered with details that bring it to life; from whimsical lights to unique mirrors, her personality shines through a striking curation of objects. Subtle veneers of eclecticism emerge throughout, manifesting as bold silver tables and ornate wall mouldings. Seth was keen on a neutral aesthetic but eschewed the idea of a space that lacked any warmth or character. She relied on texture-plush fabrics, soft throws, and intricate patterns that brought forth tactile richness, adding nuance without disrupting the simplicity of the design.

latestPosts.caption:
12 months, 13 countries later 🤍

2024 has been the most challenging and rewarding year for both my mind and my body: with pushing my body to extremes and life pushing my mind to, with losing weight to gaining my sense of self, with rediscovering passions to recognising new ones along the way, with spending time in solitude to spending time with those i love, i’m sure there are a lot of moments about the year i can look back and cringe at but none that i would like to change! 

2025, i think i’m ready for ya
